<blockquote>
<font face="Verdana" size="-1">

<P><img src="/images/BishopScantlebury.jpg" hspace=3 vspace=3 align="right" alt="Bishop Victor Scantlebury" border=0>
<p><b>Age:</b> March 31, 1945<br>
Born in Colon, Panama.  Parents: Barclay Bynoe and Diana.</p>

<p><b>Education</b>:  University of Panama, B.A. in psychology
Episcopal Theological School, 1972. Episcopal Theological Seminary of the Caribbean, Puerto Rico. MDiv. 1973.</p>

<p><b>Ordination</b>:  Deacon, October 1973, Diocese of Panama; Priest, August 1974, Diocese of Panama. Bishop Suffragan of Panama, March 15, 1991.</p>

<p><b>Family</b>:  Married Marcia V. Thomas August 11, 1973. Three children: Victoria, 25; Victor Jr., 22; Varsha, 19.</p>

<p><b>Ministry</b>:<br>
<i>Current</i>: Assistant bishop, Diocese of Chicago beginning March 1, 2000.</p>

<p><i>Prior</i>: Assisting bishop in Diocese of Mississippi 1994-2000, and rector of St. Mark and St. Christopher, Jackson, Mississippi 1995-2000. Priest-in-charge of St. John, Villa Caceres, Panama 1974-1985.  Youth coordinator for Province 9 1977-1986.  President of the Standing Committee of the Diocese of Panama 1983. Member of the Episcopal Church Executive Council 1985-1989.  Rector of St. Paul, Panama City, Panama 1985-1991.  Board of directors of the Presiding Bishop's Fund for World Relief 1988-1992.</p>

